text: The proposed rule allow studies like the Harvard Six City study to be used. EPA has not rejected or otherwise eliminated that option in anyway. In fact, the supplemental makes it clearer that such studies must be properly considered & takes comment from the public on this issue.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: The proposed science transparency rule maintains protecting confidential personal information just as other federal health agencies regularly do. This rule will ensure regulatory science underlying EPA’s actions are available in a manner sufficient for independent validation.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text:
EPA is committed to scientific integrity & transparency. Science transparency doesn't weaken science, quite the contrary.Requiring transparency will strengthen science. 
Scientists will be required to publish hypothesis & experimental data for other scientists to review & discuss
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: When EPA develops significant regs using public resources, including regs for which the public is likely to bear the cost of compliance, EPA should ensure the data & models underlying scientific studies that are pivotal to regulatory actions are available for review & reanalysis.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: Academic journals, including the Public Library of Science & the Annals of Internal Medicine already require authors to make their data available upon request. Yale & Harvard are making strides in creating publicly accessible repositories of research & clinical data.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: The proposal & supplemental will not apply to any regulations already in place. https://t.co/1B95gXBfPg
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: The NYT published story: EPA to Limit Science Used to Write Public Health Rules. This has numerous errors & is based on leaked preliminary, draft documents that are not accurate & is not the final text submitted to OMB last week for interagency review. https://t.co/1B95gXBfPg
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: To say politically appointed agency administrator's would have wide-ranging discretion over which studies to accept/reject is completely false. The proposal requires transparency & gives the discretion to use studies when information isn't available. This should be the exception.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: Science transparency does not weaken science, quite the contrary. By requiring transparency, scientists will be required to publish hypothesis & experimental data for other scientists to review & discuss, requiring the science to withstand skepticism & peer review.
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.

text: It is important to ensure science underlying EPA decisions is transparent & available for evaluation by the public & stakeholders. The proposed Science Transparency rule seeks to ensure science & data underlying EPA’s actions are publicly available for independent validation
name: U.S. EPA
description: Our mission is to protect human health and the environment.
